  "prompt": "What are some cool examples of \"Girl will be Girls\"?",
  "response": "\"Girls Will Be Girls\" is a versatile phrase that can describe various contexts from literature and film to cultural expressions and social attitudes. Here are a few interesting examples:\n\n1. **Film and TV**: The phrase is famously associated with the 2003 satirical comedy film \"Girls Will Be Girls,\" directed by Richard Day. The film follows the lives of three actresses at varying stages of their careers, all played by drag performers. It's known for its humor and for challenging gender norms.\n\n2. **Literature**: \"Girls Will Be Girls\" is also a book by Emer O'Toole, published in 2015. It\u2019s a feminist work that explores how society's expectations of femininity shape women's lives and include personal anecdotes, cultural analysis, and humor.\n\n3. **Music**: The phrase is used in song titles and lyrics across various genres, often to explore themes related to female identity, empowerment, or societal expectations.\n\n4. **Cultural Commentary**: In social contexts, \u201cGirls Will Be Girls\u201d might be used to playfully challenge or reinforce stereotypes about female behavior, sometimes pointing out double standards.\n\n5. **Art and Exhibitions**: Some artists or art exhibitions might adopt this title to explore themes of femininity, womanhood, or feminist issues, using the phrase as a way of provoking thought or commentary.\n\n6. **Fashion and Branding**: Some fashion brands or campaigns might use this slogan to capture a sense of freedom, individuality, and confidence often associated with modern femininity.\n\nThese examples show how \"Girls Will Be Girls\" can be applied across various forms of media and discussion, often serving as a platform to explore deeper societal themes.",
